Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.23,0:00:02.10,Default,Block buster did not die\Nbecause people
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.10,0:00:03.38,Default,stopped loving movies
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.78,0:00:05.61,Default,It died because the\Nbusiness model was
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.70,0:00:07.56,Default,built around a world\Nwhere inconven ience
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.56,0:00:08.49,Default,was profitable
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.12,0:00:10.82,Default,Late fees were not just\Nannoying
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.38,0:00:12.54,Default,They were part of the\Nmachine
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.19,0:00:15.09,Default,Netflix attacked the\Npain point first
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.48,0:00:17.52,Default,No due dates no store\Ntrip and
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.52,0:00:18.74,Default,no late fee surprise
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.90,0:00:21.19,Default,Then Block buster had\Ndebt
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.63,0:00:23.70,Default,thousands of stores and\Na digital shift
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.70,0:00:24.70,Default,it could not out run
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.06,0:00:27.89,Default,By 2010 the old rental\Nempire filed
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.90,0:00:28.77,Default,for bankruptcy
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.32,0:00:31.18,Default,The lesson is not that\NNetflix was
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.18,0:00:31.47,Default,magic
